[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Your code has git. Your data has what exactly? That\'s the problem. One bad CSV, one config row, one spreadsheet edit, and now your app is broken. There\'s no clean diff, no branch pull requests, no obvious roll back. This is'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'DOL. It\'s a SQL database that works just like Git. You can branch tables, edit rows, diff changes, commit them, and merge them back. Actual version control for actual data. I\'ll show you how to'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'spin this up and how to get it going in the next couple minutes. Now, we know most of the time databases are great at what being databases. They'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'store data. They let you query with SQL. But they are not great at the workflows we use every day, which is branching, reviewing, diffing, merging, rolling back, seeing exactly who changed what.'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So oftent times we pick one of two bad options. Option one is you keep the data in a real database. You get SQL indexes, constraints and structure. But when the data changes the review process is'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'usually not quite there. Then option two is we put the data in a CSV, JSON or YAML so Git can actually track it. Now you get commits and pull requests, but you lose things databases are actually'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'good at. No real SQL, weak schema enforcement, painful diffs and merges. And when someone asks, "Who changed this record?" Well, the answer is basically going to be the same. Someone with'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'database access. That\'s not any kind of real workflow. But now imagine this instead. What if you could run a branch command? Dolt branch fix this data. Dolt diff. Dolt commit. Dolt merge. Now,'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these are commands we\'re already using, but we\'re using them against your actual database tables. That\'s what Dol is doing. It\'s version control for our databases. If you enjoy coding tools'

